Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(300,300)}In 1963, a British monk sat alone in a hut in Ceylon and made a discovery. Ñāṇavīra Thera found that every moment of experience has exactly four fundamental terms: Subject, Object, Intention, and Act. Four vertices connected by six edges forming a tetrahedron. The minimal shape anything must have to exist.
